        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Virtual Community Support Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) to award grants for community-based mental health services, substance-use disorder services, and peer support services. Eligible grantees include health departments, behavioral health programs, nonprofits, and institutions of higher education.</p> <p>SAMHSA must report on the grant program, including specifically with respect to the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) emergency period.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
